---
layout: layout-base.njk
title: The Frost Panic Index | GrowByDate
description: Compare crop-location combinations with the highest fall frost pressure.
canonical: "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/the-frost-panic-index/"
---

{% set board = frostPanicIndex %}
{% set top = board.top %}
{% set lowest = board.lowestDisplayed %}

<section class="card leaderboardHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Frost pressure ranking</p>
  <h1>The Frost Panic Index</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Some crop-location combinations are much closer to the first fall frost than they appear from calendar days alone. This ranking highlights crops and places where timing, heat, and frost margin are especially tight.
  </p>

  <div class="leaderboardStatGrid" aria-label="Ranking summary">
    {% if top %}
      <div class="leaderboardStat">
        <span class="statLabel">Highest panic</span>
        <strong>{{ top.cropName }} in {{ top.cityName }}</strong>
        <span>{{ top.score }}/100 · {{ top.label }}</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if lowest %}
      <div class="leaderboardStat">
        <span class="statLabel">Lowest shown</span>
        <strong>{{ lowest.cropName }} in {{ lowest.cityName }}</strong>
        <span>{{ lowest.score }}/100 · {{ lowest.label }}</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="leaderboardStat">
      <span class="statLabel">Combinations shown</span>
      <strong>Top {{ board.entries.length }} of {{ board.totalCandidates }}</strong>
      <span>Highest-pressure crop and city pairs</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>The ranking</h2>
  <p>
    Higher scores mean less margin before fall frost. These are not impossible crops; they are combinations where variety choice, planting timing, and season extension matter most.
  </p>

  <div class="tableWrap leaderboardTableWrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Rank</th>
          <th>Crop and location</th>
          <th>Panic score</th>
          <th>Crop fit</th>
          <th>GDD margin</th>
          <th>Frost-free days</th>
          <th>First fall frost</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for row in board.entries %}
          <tr>
            <td><strong>#{{ row.rank }}</strong></td>
            <td>
              <a href="{{ row.url }}"><strong>{{ row.cropName }} in {{ row.cityName }}</strong></a><br>
              <span class="small muted">{{ row.regionName }}{% if row.country == "canada" %}, Canada{% elseif row.country == "usa" %}, U.S.{% endif %}</span>
            </td>
            <td>
              <strong>{{ row.score }}/100</strong><br>
              <span class="fitBadge fitBadge-{{ row.badgeClass }}">{{ row.label }}</span>
            </td>
            <td>{{ row.cropFitScore }}/100<br><span class="small muted">{{ row.cropFitLabel }}</span></td>
            <td>{% if row.gddMargin >= 0 %}+{% endif %}{{ row.gddMargin }} GDD</td>
            <td>{{ row.frostFreeDays }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.fallFrost }}</td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card leaderboardCallout">
  <h2>What this ranking means</h2>
  <p>
    Frost panic is about margin. A crop can be possible and still be stressful if expected maturity lands close to first fall frost or depends on fast varieties and exact timing.
  </p>
  <p>
    Use this ranking to spot where a crop deserves extra planning: earlier starts, faster varieties, row cover, warm microclimates, or a backup harvest plan.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Methodology</h2>
  <p>{{ board.methodology }}</p>
  <p>{{ board.caveat }}</p>
  <p class="small">
    Download: <a href="/assets/data/rankings/the-frost-panic-index.json">Frost Panic Index JSON</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": {{ board.title | dump | safe }},
  "description": {{ board.description | dump | safe }},
  "url": "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/the-frost-panic-index/",
  "numberOfItems": {{ board.entries.length }},
  "itemListElement": [
    {% for row in board.entries %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ row.rank }},
        "name": {{ (row.cropName ~ " in " ~ row.cityName ~ " frost panic score") | dump | safe }},
        "url": {{ (site.url ~ row.url) | dump | safe }}
      }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  ]
}
</script>
